<item>
            <title>[SOCIALFB-138] Jackson Map Exception on checkinposts</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SOCIALFB-138</link>
                <project id="10607" key="SOCIALFB">Spring Social Facebook</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some checkins do not provide a complete location mapping, only a String telling the location. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest adding a location deserializer like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	@Override&lt;br/&gt;
	public Location deserialize(JsonParser jp, DeserializationContext ctxt) throws IOException, JsonProcessingException {&lt;br/&gt;
		try&lt;/p&gt;
{
			Location node = jp.readValueAs(Location.class);
			return node;
		}
&lt;p&gt;catch (Exception e)&lt;/p&gt;
{
			Location location = new Location(jp.getText());
			return null;
		}
&lt;p&gt;	}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
