                            <comment id="93912" author="habuma" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 13:29:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good, but can you provide a snippet of JSON showing how such a checkin would look? Preferably a real checkin (or at least a real location from a checkin) so that I can have a realistic bit of test data to test against.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="93913" author="habuma" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 13:54:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, I was able to dig around in some of my own checkins to find a couple of examples. These String-only checkin locations do seem to be rare. I had to go back two years to find a couple of them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="93929" author="jachzen" created="Thu, 26 Sep 2013 01:55:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Facebook documentation is a bit fuzzy:&lt;br/&gt;
